, aesthetics, and ethics. Roberts brings these themes to our attention, shows how they are integrated into the work as a whole, and demonstrates the relevance of these topics for our own times.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aTaoism. 7aRELIGION / Taoism (see also PHILOSOPHY / Taoist).2bisacsh  aacademic.  aaesthetics.  aancient history.  aancient world.  achina.  achinese history.  achinese literature.  achinese poetry.  achinese scholarship.  acommentary.  acosmology.  acultural history.  acultural studies.  adao de jing.  aethics.  ainspirational.  ainspiring.  aliterary.  aliterature.  aphilosopher.  aphilosophy.  apoet.  apoetry.  apolitical.  apolitics.  areligion.  areligious studies.  arevelation.  ascholarly.  asocial commentary.  asocial history.  asocial studies.  astatecraft.  atranslation.  auniversal.  aworld history.1 aRoberts, Moss, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052020555040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093121340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520931213423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520931213/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY